targets.rawSql:
SELECT value=count(*)
  FROM [dbo].[sqlwatch_meta_check]
  WHERE [sql_instance] = '$sql_instance'
  AND [last_check_status] <> 'OK'
  AND [last_check_status] <> 'WARNING'

SELECT value=count(*)
  FROM [dbo].[sqlwatch_meta_check]
  WHERE [sql_instance] = '$sql_instance'
  AND [last_check_status] = 'CHECK ERROR'

SELECT
      [time]=GETUTCDATE() 
      ,metric = check_description
      ,[value] = 1
  FROM [dbo].[vw_sqlwatch_report_dim_check]
  WHERE 1=1 --$__timeFilter(snapshot_time)
  and check_name = '$Check'
  AND [sql_instance] = '$sql_instance'

SELECT  [check_name] = [check_name]
        ,[last_check_value] = convert(varchar(max),[last_check_value])
        ,status = CASE [last_check_status] 
        WHEN 'CRITICAL' THEN 2
        WHEN 'WARNING' THEN 1
        WHEN 'OK' THEN 0
        ELSE 3 END
  FROM [dbo].[vw_sqlwatch_report_dim_check] with (nolock)
  WHERE  [sql_instance] = '$sql_instance'
  and [last_check_status] in ($Status)
  order by case when last_check_status = 'OK' then dateadd(month,-1,last_check_date_local) else last_check_date_local end desc

panels.description: The colours are a bit off but this is just this panel's and Grafana's limitation.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT 
      [time] = $__timeGroup([snapshot_time], 1s)
      ,[OK] = case [check_status] when 'OK' then 1 else 0 end
      ,[WARNING] = case [check_status] when 'WARNING' then 2 else 0 end
      ,[CRITICAL] = case [check_status] when 'CRITICAL' then 3 else 0 end
      ,[ERROR] = case [check_status] when 'CHECK ERROR' then 4 else 0 end
      --,[OTHER] = case when [check_status] not in ('OK','WARNING','CRITICAL','CHECK ERROR') then 5 else 0 end
  FROM [dbo].[vw_sqlwatch_report_fact_check]
  WHERE $__timeFilter(snapshot_time)
  and check_name = '$Check'
  AND [sql_instance] = '$sql_instance'
ORDER BY
  time ASC
